{
  "texts": [
    "Currently, the content poisoning attack is the most debatable area of interest for researchers due to its seriousness.",
    "As mentioned earlier NDN uses cache for storing the copies of contents locally for future use to provide efficient and reliable content distribution to consumer.",
    "However, a malicious user can change and modify the original copy of the content stored in the cache of the routers.",
    "Similarly, a malicious user can inject fake and poison content into the NDN router inside the network.",
    "In other words, an attacker can modify a signature of the content or its metadata (provider signature, show himself as a valid provider)."
  ]
}